<br /><h2>Small Batch Black Pepper Parmesan Chive Biscuit Recipe</h2><br />
<div>
    <div>
        <img src="~/RecipeImageFiles/2_1.jpg" style="width:70%;margin:auto" />
    </div>
    <div>
        <h3>Ingredients</h3>
        <p>1 cup flour</p>
        <p>1/2 packed cup shredded parmesan</p>
        <p>1 teaspoon baking powder</p>
        <p>1/2 teaspoon salt</p>
        <p>1/4 teaspoon baking soda</p>
        <p>1/4 teaspoon black pepper, plus extra for the tops if desired</p>
        <p>2 tablespoons thinly sliced chives</p>
        <p>1/3 cup sour cream, chilled</p>
        <p>1/4 cup plus 1 tablespoon milk, chilled</p>
        <p>2 tablespoons unsalted butter, melted for brushing on biscuit tops</p>
    </div>
    <div>
        <h3>Recipe</h3>
        <p>
            Preheat the oven to 400°F.

            In a bowl, whisk together the flour, parmesan, baking powder, salt, baking soda, pepper, and chives.

            Stir in the sour cream until the mixture resembles coarse grains. Add the chilled milk and fold until it just comes together.

            Scoop the batter by the 1/4 cup (I use a ice cream scoop) onto parchment paper lined sheets, 1 inch apart. Bake for 15 minutes, remove and brush with melted butter. Bake for another 5-7 minutes or until golden brown.
        </p>
    </div>

